product.shortDescription:
Equate 70% Isopropyl Alcohol Antiseptic is the perfect solution for cleaning and sanitizing skin and surfaces. The 70% isopropyl alcohol solution is a powerful agent for cleaning cuts, burns, scrapes, and scratches while also promoting a speedy recovery. It is also excellent for cleaning oils, greases, glues, and inks from surfaces. This 32-ounce bottle is ideal for every first aid kit at home, in your car, or at the office. For those who must self-administer injections for medical conditions like diabetes, this solution is perfect for sterilizing both your needle and the injection site. Whether you're sterilizing a wound, or simply want a fresh, clean home free of germs, this cleaning and sanitizing solution is the answer. For whenever you need a helping hand, bring home a 32-ounce bottle of Equate 70% Isopropyl Alcohol Antiseptic today.

Making the right health decisions can be challenging. With a complete range of products and simple solutions, equate allows you to take care of your family with confidence.

product.name: Equate 70% Isopropyl Alcohol Antiseptic, 32 fl oz

directions.name: Instructions
directions.value: Clean affected area. Apply small amount of this product on the area 1-3 times daily. If bandaged, let dry first. May be covered with a sterile bandage.

indications.name: Stop Use Indications
indications.value: Stop use and ask a doctor if condition persists or gets worse. For external use only. If taken internally, serious gastric disturbances will result. Flammable, keep away from fire or flame. Use only in a well-ventilated area; fumes may be toxic. Ask a doctor before use if you have deep or puncture wounds, animal bites or serious burns. Do not get into eyes. Do not apply over large areas of the body. Do not use longer than one week unless directed by doctor. Keep out of reach of children. In case of ingestion, get medical help or contact a Poison Control Center right away.

indications.name: Health Concern
indications.value: Cuts & Abrasions; First Aid Antiseptic; Infection; Sanitizer; Cleansing Agent

ingredients.name: Ingredients
ingredients.value: Active Ingredient: Isopropyl alcohol (70% conc.). Inactive Ingredient: purified water.

customerReviews.reviewText: The product came fast it was sealed good price and good amount for what I pay, the only inconvenience was the delivery, the delivery person left the box by the entrance of the stairs of the building, he could put outside my apartment since the building hall are open up no walls. Thanks to my neighbor that saw it and save it for me.

I recommend you buying this online. Its much larger than the ones they sell in the stores if you can find it in the stores. This is great for making sanitizer wipes. I also ad hand sanitizer to a small bottle and pour this alcohol in it. I carry this bottle ever where.  So buy it online,  you'll come out better.
customerReviews.reviewTitle: the best value for your money

customerReviews.reviewText:
We've ordered this Equate 70% Isopropyl Alcohol 2-pack for delivery through Walmart.com a few times since the COVID-19 pandemic began. The product appears to be as advertised, and the bottles are well packed and have arrived intact with no spillage. We haven't run out of disinfecting wipes yet (knock on wood), but with the short supply predicted to continue, we have a plan to make our own disinfecting wipes with Isopropyl, paper towels, some lovely essential oils, and a couple other ingredients if the need should arise.
If you're going to order Isopropyl Alcohol for delivery, you can't beat the Walmart.com price - I have checked. Since the COVID-19 pandemic began, we have been avoiding public spaces such as brick-and-mortar stores as much as we can. So far it seems to work well for us if we add a two-pack of 70% Isopropyl to the cart whenever we make a Walmart.com order - this way we know that we always have some on hand when we need it.  :-)

customerReviews.reviewText: I love using this especially with this coronavirus pandemic! Its so hard to find any disinfecting sprays
It's the one I like 90 % is too strong
product seemed intact but box was delivered with the top torn open. Not sure how this happened. Got package off front porch within 20-30 min of delivery

During Covid alcohol was so widely used in homes and especially hospitals you were lucky if you could find any anywhere. I try to keep a few bottles on hand now because it doesn't expire. I use it for disinfecting wounds , cleaning skin after insect bites and especially insect bites. Ii like to now keep some in a spray bottle to disinfect surfaces .  I like it because it isn't strong like bleach and doesn't bleach everything it touches. I do not like the idea of the larger bottles. I wish they would carry it in a smaller bottle like they use to. Add it to a little dawn and water in a spray bottle for cleaning works great
